        "Yaqeen's strength lies in its ability to scale intellectual content globally. With <cite id=\"4\">100 million views across platforms</cite>, the organization demonstrates massive digital reach. This is supported by a robust governance structure consisting of a <cite id=\"11\">13-member board</cite> and a <cite id=\"12\">documented Theory of Change</cite> that guides its research priorities. Financially, the organization has shown steady growth with a <cite id=\"13\">3-year revenue CAGR of 3.5%</cite>, reaching <cite id=\"2\">$8,759,241 in total revenue</cite> by the 2023 tax year."
      ],
      "summary": "Yaqeen Research Institute Inc is a global non-profit research organization dedicated to addressing contemporary challenges through <cite id=\"1\">high-quality Islamic research and educational resources</cite>. The institute focuses on dismantling doubts and nurturing conviction by producing peer-reviewed research papers, curriculum, and multimedia content. In 2023, the organization reported <cite id=\"2\">total revenue of $8,759,241</cite>, reflecting a stable financial base for its intellectual output. Yaqeen maintains a <cite id=\"3\">96/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite>, signaling strong institutional health and transparency. Its reach is extensive, with digital engagement metrics showing <cite id=\"4\">100,000,000 total views across platforms</cite> and <cite id=\"5\">37,075 students utilizing its specialized curriculum</cite>. Beyond digital content, the organization has historically engaged in humanitarian efforts, including <cite id=\"6\">medical mission treatments and orphan sponsorship</cite>, though its primary focus remains capacity building through knowledge. The institute operates with a <cite id=\"7\">86.1% program expense ratio</cite> according to recent financial filings, ensuring that donor contributions are directed toward its core mission of research and education.",
